  "prompt": "Do anti-money laundering regulations exist?",
  "response": "Yes, anti-money laundering (AML) regulations exist in many countries worldwide. These regulations are designed to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income. Key examples include:\n\n1. United States\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA)\n- USA PATRIOT Act\n\n2. European Union\n- Anti-Money Laundering Directives (AMLD)\n- Comprehensive regulatory framework\n\n3. International standards\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Global guidelines for combating money laundering\n\nThese regulations typically require financial institutions to:\n- Conduct customer due diligence\n- Report suspicious transactions\n- Maintain transaction records\n- Implement internal control systems\n- Screen customers against watchlists\n\nPenalties for non-compliance can include significant fines and potential criminal prosecution.",
